-- Bahrain Mega Industrial City to Cost $15.9 Billion, Alayam Says
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-07-11T08:48:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-11/bahrain-mega-industrial-city-to-cost-15-9-billion-alayam-says.html
Construction and development costs
of Bahrain’s planned mega industrial city are estimated at 6
billion dinars ($16 billion), Alayam reported, citing Hassan Fakhru, the kingdom’s industry and commerce minister.  The government has finished a feasibility study of the
planned city, which will be constructed on 93 square kilometers
of land, Fakhru told the  newspaper . The city is expected to
generate 5 billion dinars a year by 2040 and provide 240,000
jobs, Alayam cited Fakhru as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Manama at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
